FBIS4-57134 "drlat093_q_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 Paraguay Brazilian Military Takes Bridge From Police Brazilian Military Takes Bridge From Police PY1205123594 Asuncion ABC COLOR in Spanish 12 May 94 p 12 PY1205123594 Asuncion ABC COLOR Spanish BFN [Unattributed report from the ABC COLOR Regional Bureau] [Excerpt] Last night, the Brazilian Armed Forces occupied the Foz de Iguazu [Brazil] side of the Friendship Bridge to guarantee the free circulation given the indefinite strike of the Brazilian Federal Police, who have been on strike for more than 30 days. Foz de Iguazu businessmen have lost more than 85 billion guaranies [figure as published] as a result of a drop in the flow of tourists due to the strike. Federal Tax Office inspectors have also joined the strike. Last night, military forces took control of the Brazilian side of the Friendship Bridge due to the prolonged strike of that country's Federal Police, thus confirming persistent rumors that circulated last night. [passage omitted]
